76561198081788004,Recommended,232890,12233396,"Posted: 25 September, 2014",all,Alvagor,"Stronghold Crusader 2 is a RTS game developed by Firefly Studios and released on the 23 September 2014.Merits:-Good strategy game-New 3D Graphics Engine, good graphic, accurate animations and effects-Good tutorial (including ""tutorial campaign"")-Decent descriptions about soldiers, buildings ecc.-Very nice as a coop game-Realistic sieges (gradual destruction of defence's walls, fires, defence's walls usable by soldiers, for example)-Decent system of economy/popularityDefects:-You can't choose the difficulty level of the AI (!)-There aren't number-based descriptions about, for example, the health or the attack strength of soldiers, or even the resistance of buildings, but only simple text descriptions about everything.-There aren't random generated maps, but only made maps done by developers, and they aren't so much, in my opinion.-Some maps have stone and iron deposits only in determined points of the map, where you CAN'T build your mine because  that deposit ""it's not in your territory""-Low amount of campaigns-Not really an exciting game if played in singleplayer (but for this there is the multiplayer)-This games is missing some stuff about the old Stronghold CrusaderConclusions: Even if this game has a lot of defects, it can give you a nice gaming experience because it's a very studied game with tactical parts and other things that make this a really nice strategy game, especially if played in multiplayer with other players.Vote: 8/10"
